population exchanges in the modern era events at stanford population exchanges in the modern era facebook twitter email print add to calendar population exchanges in the modern era a roundtable discussion with matthew frank lecturer in international history at university of leeds uk catherine gousseff researcher at centre national de la recherche scientifique cnrs the roundtable engages the causes courses and consequences of the policy of mass population exchanges that have shaped the political and ethnographic boundaries of modern eurasia matthew frank is a lecturer in international history at leeds university he earned both his master's and doctorate in modern history from st antony's college 2000 and 2005 respectively catherine gousseff is a researcher at cnrs she focuses primarily on russian emigration and history when wednesday february 8 2012 5 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where humanities center levinthal hall map audience general public faculty staff students tags other sponsor the europe center the department of history mediterranean studies forum center for russian east european & eurasian studies and the stanford humanities center contact 736 8169 burcak stanford edu admission open to the public rsvp http europe stanford edu events registration 6961 permalink http events stanford edu events 300 30061 more info last modified december 29 2011
